        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 6:11PM CDT by NWS Lubbock TX</headline>
        <description>At 610 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Dimmitt, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dimmitt, Hart, and Nazareth.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
